      <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Historical overview</div>
          <h2>From municipal service to regional provider</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        Beaumont Animal Control has evolved through several distinct
        operational periods.
      </p>

      <p>
        The available public record shows that Beaumont maintained its own
        municipal Animal Control function while also developing contractual
        relationships that extended services beyond the City's boundaries.
      </p>

      <p>
        The most clearly documented regional relationship involved the
        City of Calimesa. Official records establish that Beaumont was
        providing Animal Control services to Calimesa beginning in 2010,
        with the relationship continuing through June 30, 2023.
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section compact alt">
    <div class="wrap">

      <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Timeline</div>
          <h2>Key documented milestones</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="story-grid">

        <article class="story-card">
          <span>2010</span>
          <h3>Calimesa Service Begins</h3>
          <p>
            Later official City records identify July 1, 2010 as the
            beginning of Beaumont's Animal Control service relationship
            with the City of Calimesa.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="story-card">
          <span>2018</span>
          <h3>Three Authorized FTE</h3>
          <p>
            Available budget records identify 3.0 Animal Control
            full-time-equivalent positions in FY 2018.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="story-card">
          <span>2019</span>
          <h3>Staffing at Two FTE</h3>
          <p>
            By FY 2019, available budget records show authorized Animal
            Control staffing at 2.0 FTE. The reason for this reduction
            remains an identified research gap.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="story-card">
          <span>2021</span>
          <h3>Regional Agreements Continue</h3>
          <p>
            Beaumont approved a new Calimesa Animal Control agreement
            covering July 1, 2021 through June 30, 2023.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="story-card">
          <span>2021</span>
          <h3>Shelter Agreement Renewed</h3>
          <p>
            Beaumont approved a multi-year shelter services agreement
            with the Ramona Humane Society in September 2021.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="story-card">
          <span>2023</span>
          <h3>Calimesa Service Ends</h3>
          <p>
            Beaumont's contracted Animal Control services for Calimesa
            concluded on June 30, 2023.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="story-card">
          <span>2024</span>
          <h3>Sheltering Model Changes</h3>
          <p>
            Changes involving the shelter provider and Beaumont's
            agreement altered certain intake services, including
            owner-surrender services.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="story-card">
          <span>Today</span>
          <h3>Beaumont-Focused Model</h3>
          <p>
            The current program is more focused on Animal Control
            services within Beaumont while continuing to rely on
            contracted sheltering and licensing support.
          </p>
        </article>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section compact">
    <div class="wrap">

      <div class="section-heading">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Regional service</div>
          <h2>The Calimesa relationship</h2>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="change-grid">

        <article class="change-card">
          <h3>Documented beginning</h3>
          <p>
            Later official records identify July 1, 2010 as the effective
            beginning of Beaumont's Animal Control services for Calimesa.
          </p>
          <p>
            The original 2010 agreement has not been located in the
            digital records reviewed for this Intelligence Center.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="change-card">
          <h3>2021 agreement</h3>
          <p>
            On June 1, 2021, the Beaumont City Council considered a
            renewed Animal Control services agreement with Calimesa.
          </p>
          <p>
            The agreement covered the period from July 1, 2021 through
            June 30, 2023 and continued an already established regional
            service relationship.
          </p>
        </article>

